"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"* my new goal is to maximize fluidity\\n  * i want my experience to be as frictionless, spontaneous, and in-flow as possible\\n  * a better way to say this is: i want to have fun\\n* i’ve found that any self-imposed rigid structures inevitably collapse\\n* my trading ethos is along these lines:\\n  * “every day, i assume every position i have is wrong” — Paul Tudor Jones\\n  * i am infinitely ignorant, per the arguments of Naval Ravikant\\n  * i disregard sunken costs; there is no such thing as wasted effort\\n* according to a far more experienced fund manager, with my tiny portfolio, it’s better to make plays with tactical, in-and-out opportunities such as flipping shitcoins rather than the long-term perspective i’m currently deploying\\n  * this is because my sizing is nimble and can easily play in smaller opportunities as needed\\n* until i’m a whale, i can leverage my strength of unlimited deployability\\n  * a large fund such as 3AC can’t act without incurring huge slippage, and opportunities of MCAP < 5-10 million aren’t even worth their time\\n* this is a convincing argument to me, and at the same time i think it makes sense for me to maintain (and develop invalidation points for) my current holdings\\n  * until i find invalidations for my original theses or superior opportunities, i’ll hold my current positioning\\n  * at the same time, i can use my remaining capital to gain familiarity with this faster, tactical approach: the grey jackal is an opportunistic omnivore\",\"timestamp\":1634274259,\"title\":\"trading attitude refresh\"},\"digest\":\"UOiZfaMCrRzJ0Jr4InICgaq4y-QGkJGH3z8-VaFJT5E\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0xdF3AB3adB9F679d71b9A22ab77565b1FF3A5047D\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"_JiuWO731F3bhDAPMgNFNaovDkRTPSt89uP_9frEql4\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"bHF0APHB54AF9Lt0UPWhYOciyTUJwUKTBwpcE4mjYro\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"lIPl4ylOb